Welcome back to The Daily Courant, your afternoon medley of Puck=E2=80=99s =
best new reporting.

=C2=A0

First up today, Eriq Gardner dissects a pair of lawsuits rattling Hollywood=
 in the Trump II era: actors Rockmond Dunbar and Ingo Rademacher=E2=80=99s =
parallel Covid-era cases against Disney. Both seek to challenge the industr=
y=E2=80=99s political status quo. And both, not surprisingly, have an R.F.K=
=2E Jr. twist=E2=80=A6

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Marion Maneker sees a cultural warning in the Met=E2=
=80=99s new exhibition of German romanticist Caspar David Friedrich. Sarah =
Shapiro prophesies trouble with Gap=E2=80=99s latest supposed revival. And =
John Heilemann turns to Harvard Law professor Laurence Tribe to explain why=
 the courts may be the last safeguard against Trump=E2=80=99s divisive
agenda.=C2=A0

